replies.bodyText:
I don't think we have a util in Java for this at the moment. The field mask should only consist of field names in a dotted notation. Following json payload:
{
  'parentField1': 'some value',
  'parentField2': 'another value',
  'parentField3': {
    'childField1': 'yet another value'
  }
}

should become:
['parentField1', 'parentField2', 'parentField3.childField1']

You can also look at the unit tests of the Node.js utils for more examples.

